"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Ray of Enfeeblement</a></span></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">5th</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.oyE5nVppa5mde5gT\" data-id=\"oyE5nVppa5mde5gT\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Animate Dead</a>, <a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.XXUDGFELgoskdOD0\" data-id=\"XXUDGFELgoskdOD0\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Fear</a></span></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">7th</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.pybg5MNc3lkerH4Y\" data-id=\"pybg5MNc3lkerH4Y\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Blight</a>, <a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.VtCXMdyM6mAdIJZb\" data-id=\"VtCXMdyM6mAdIJZb\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Death Ward</a></span></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">9th</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.91Sw6vOIaO7U8DvM\" data-id=\"91Sw6vOIaO7U8DvM\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Dominate Person</a>, <a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.NmoRmM1mhuM3pqnY\" data-id=\"NmoRmM1mhuM3pqnY\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Wall of Stone</a></span></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><img src=\"modules/under-the-harvest-moons/Assets/Art/Broken_Bone_Domain.jpg\" width=\"284\" height=\"486\" /><p></p><h2><strong>Strong of Bone</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.o0XBsgD40oC0Kfcp]{Strong of Bone}</p><p><em>1st-level Broken Bone Domain feature</em></p><p>Ecrassus strengthens the skeletal warrior waiting within you. You gain proficiency in martial weapons. Additionally, as long as you aren’t wearing armor, your Armor Class is equal to 10 + your Wisdom modifier + your Dexterity modifier. You may use a shield and still gain this benefit.</p><p></p><h2><strong>Channel Divinity:</strong></h2><h3>Break the Weak</h3><p>@UUID[Item.g1tt43FwXw9xLWYF]{Channel Divinity: Break the Weak}</p><p><em>2nd-level Broken Bone Domain feature</em></p><p>You can channel your dark god’s power to destroy those weaker than you. As a bonus action, you may choose one creature you can see within 30 feet of you who has been damaged. Until the end of your next turn, the next time you or an ally hits the target creature with an attack, the creature takes an additional amount of necrotic damage equal to your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier.</p><p></p><h2><strong>Reap the Marrow</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.0WwCxxlkCsCEuoRU]{Reap the Marrow}</p><p><em>6th-level Broken Bone Domain feature</em></p><p>You lay claim to the bones of the fallen. You may use any spell or ability that would allow you to create or raise a creature with the undead type to create a skeleton, no matter the condition of the targeted remains or normal specifications of the spell or ability. Additionally, when a creature within 30 feet of you dies, you may use your reaction to immediately cast animate dead on that creature as long as you have the spell slot available.</p><p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus. You regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p><p></p><h2><strong>Divine Strike</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.qcR1hASR1kfTgRL8]{Divine Strike}</p><p><em>8th-level Broken Bone Domain feature</em></p><p>You gain the ability to infuse your weapon strikes with Ecrassus’s foul energy. Once on each of your turns, when you hit a creature with a weapon attack, you can cause the attack to deal an extra 1d8 necrotic damage to the target. When you reach 14th level, the extra damage increases to 2d8.</p><p></p><h2><strong>High Priest of the Throng</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.40I3u7d6AIp8wF5I]{High Priest of the Throng}</p><p><em>17th-level Broken Bone Domain feature</em></p><p>You have become one of Ecrassus’s most trusted servants. As long as you aren’t wearing armor, your Armor Class increases to 12 + your Wisdom modifier + your Dexterity modifier. You may use a shield and still gain this benefit.</p><p>Additionally, you and all skeletons under your control gain resistance to bludgeoning damage.</p><p></p><img src=\"modules/under-the-harvest-moons/Assets/Art/highpriestess.jpg\" />","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":400000,"name":"Druid Circle: Circle of the Unseely","type":"text","_id":"T60tHd6HBnOGW9s2","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p></p><blockquote><p>“Their willingness to give themselves fully to forces of darkness, natural or otherwise, have left them twisted and lost. They are the antithesis of what we, as druids, strive for. They are abominations.”</p><p>- AarriannaKahn, High Druid</p></blockquote><p></p><p>Druids of the Circle of the Unseely go far beyond simply interacting with the fey and seek to make true and lasting covenants with members of the Gloaming Courts. These druids aspire to what they see as true ascendance in the natural world by casting off their mortal ties and giving themselves fully over to the darkest sways of the Feywild.</p><p>Members of the Circle of the Unseely are not looked highly upon by other druids, who see their preference for communing with dark or sinister fey influences as unbalanced at best and flagrantly dangerous at worst. And although not all members of this druid circle see themselves as evil, they all gleefully revel in the discomfort and unease they instill in those around them.</p><p></p><h2><strong>Circle Spells</strong></h2><p><em>2nd-level Circle of the Unseely feature</em></p><p>Your covenant with the Unseely fey has gifted you with access to certain spells. At 2nd level, you learn the @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.cdrYKaFi98YWaBMw]{Vicious Mockery} cantrip. At 3rd, 5th, 7th, and 9th level, you gain access to the spells listed for that level in the Circle of the Unseely Spells table.</p><p>Once you gain access to one of these spells, you always have it prepared, and it doesn't count against the number of spells you can prepare each day. If you gain access to a spell that doesn't appear on the druid spell list, the spell is nonetheless a druid spell for you.</p><p></p><table border=\"1\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:540px;border-collapse:collapse;background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-tertiary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-tertiary);margin:0.5em 0px;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><thead style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);color:var(--color-text-light-highlight);text-shadow:1px 1px var(--color-shadow-dark);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\"><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Druid Level</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Spells</span></td></tr></thead><tbody style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">3rd</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.UDUnlfPsOAbq2RSE\" data-id=\"UDUnlfPsOAbq2RSE\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Blur</a>, <a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.1N8dDMMgZ1h1YJ3B\" data-id=\"1N8dDMMgZ1h1YJ3B\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Invisibility</a></span></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">5th</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.pO4zGe5LmFIYqJiL\" data-id=\"pO4zGe5LmFIYqJiL\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Bestow Curse</a>, <a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.6g3WLOZ2u0EbaLAd\" data-id=\"6g3WLOZ2u0EbaLAd\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Hypnotic Pattern</a></span></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">7th</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.P6f1PPKPd9BCb742\" data-id=\"P6f1PPKPd9BCb742\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Compulsion</a>, <a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.tEpDmYZNGc9f5OhJ\" data-id=\"tEpDmYZNGc9f5OhJ\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Greater Invisibility</a>, </span></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">9th</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.JQyigMNPiDnGI18b\" data-id=\"JQyigMNPiDnGI18b\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Geas</a>, <a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.MBMaQLwoy05qzMJ3\" data-id=\"MBMaQLwoy05qzMJ3\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Mislead</a></span></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><img src=\"modules/under-the-harvest-moons/Assets/Art/circle_ofthe_unseely.png\" width=\"292\" height=\"392\" /><p></p><h2><strong>Unseely Ichor</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.4zvstkSy8xWt7QJC]{Unseely Ichor}</p><p><em>2nd-level Circle of the Unseely feature</em></p><p>You are granted unsavory abilities tied to your burgeoning unseely nature. You gain a pool of fey energy represented by a number of d6s equal to your druid level.</p><p>When you are hit with a melee attack or a creature attempts to grapple you, you may use your reaction to cover yourself in a thick, viscous slime. You may determine the effect of the slime from the below options. You remain covered in the slime until you dismiss it, and you may select a different effect each time you use this reaction.</p><p></p><blockquote><p>@UUID[Item.d5xOszeT4J4sKFfD]{Acidic Slime}</p><p>You may spend a number of dice equal to your druid level or less to inflict acid damage. The targeted creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw against your spell save DC or take acid damage equal to the amount rolled.</p></blockquote><p></p><blockquote><p>@UUID[Item.z3dZwEEz6A7ufZxk]{Resistant Slime}</p><p>You may spend a number of dice equal to half your druid level or less (rounded up). Reduce the amount of damage you would take from bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage by the amount rolled.</p></blockquote><p></p><blockquote><p>@UUID[Item.OmjPZ1n6FpNtnn2Y]{Tenacious Slime}</p><p>You may spend a number of dice equal to half your rolled to druid level or less (rounded up). Add the amount Strength (Athletics) checks made to grapple the target creature. You regain all expended dice when you finish a long rest.</p></blockquote><h2><strong>Shadow Dance</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.hZdZZbXiC6rNJsuJ]{Shadow Dance}</p><p><em>6th-level Circle of the Unseely feature</em></p><p>You are able to harness your unruly presence to cause the shadows of your enemies to turn against their masters. As an action, choose a number of creatures within 30 feet of you equal to your proficiency bonus. The chosen creatures’ shadows separate from them and begin to attack them viciously. The creatures must make a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failure, the creature’s speed is halved, and they take 4d8 force damage from their shadows. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage, and their speed is not affected. The shadows continue to rebel and slow the affected creatures for a number of rounds equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of one). Affected creatures may repeat their saving throws at the start of each of their turns. Once a creature has succeeded on its saving throw, its speed returns to normal.</p><p>Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a short or long rest.</p><p></p><h2><strong>Courtly Seeming</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.gEBrG8jzpXwF4COz]{Courtly Seeming}</p><p><em>10th-level Circle of the Unseely feature</em></p><p>You can assume the guise of a Lord of the Fey Courts to terrify or beguile the creatures around you. As an action, choose a number of creatures within 60 feet of you equal to your proficiency bonus that can see and hear you. The chosen creatures must make a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failed save, the creature is either charmed or frightened for 1 minute. Affected creatures may repeat their saving throw at the start of each of their turns, and once they have successfully made their saving throw, they cannot be affected by this ability again for 24 hours.</p><p>Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a short or long rest.</p><p></p><h2><strong>Embrace of the Gloam</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.bobXsjciUxNMTPWv]{Embrace of the Gloam}</p><p><em>14th-level Circle of the Unseely feature</em></p><p>You have completely given yourself over to the influences of the unseely, and they have accepted you as one of their own. You can no longer be charmed or frightened, and you gain resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage from nonmagical attacks.</p><p>Additionally, as a bonus action, you may teleport to an unoccupied space within 30 feet of you, provided that both the space you’re teleporting from and your destination are in dim light or darkness. The destination does not need to be within line of sight.</p><p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses of it when you finish a long rest.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":500000,"name":"Ranger Archetype: Veil Watchman","type":"text","_id":"qXGjp2HBv4VQpeSw","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px 0.5em 10px;padding:0px 0px 0px 20px;border-left:3px solid var(--color-border-light-tertiary);font-style:italic;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><em><br class=\"Apple-interchange-newline\" />“Mortal minds will never truly comprehend those great and terrible things that lurk beyond the veil. Our job is to place our bodies and spirits between man and that knowledge.”</em></span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><em>- Quinarys Ellavoss, Veil Watchman</em></span></p></blockquote><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">The threats that undead visit upon mortals are terrible in scope and variety. From the shambling corpses risen from their graves to the bloodthirsty prowlers of rooftops and alleyways, those creatures cursed to roam long after their hearts have stopped beating are the bane of all living things. Too often, though, the most insidious of these undead are allowed to tread the realms of mortals unnoticed, slipping through man-made barriers to torment the minds and hearts of those within. It is truly a blessing that the Veil Watchmen have dedicated themselves to protecting the veil that separates specters and men.</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Where other rangers concern themselves with guarding humanity against the natural realms, Veil Watchmen have tasked themselves with protecting mortal souls from incorporeal spirits. Although their earthen magics are often effective in the pursuit of their incorporeal foes, a Veil Watchman will utilize any tools and techniques necessary to safeguard mortals. Alchemy, divine blessings, esoteric tomes, and arcane artifacts—attained legally or illicitly—are all equal parts of their ghost hunting arsenal. This willingness to experiment leads them to ally themselves with an assortment of churches, secret societies, and guilds. Anyone who stands between the Prime Material and the dangers of the Ethereal is counted among the friends of the Veil Watchmen.</span></p><p></p><p>@UUID[Item.tdJSZPN86AR3IvZo]{Veil Watchman}</p><p></p><section id=\"secret-8ApTCeOpfgQbqj5d\" class=\"secret\"><p><em><strong>GM NOTES: ORGANIZATIONS</strong></em></p><p>Although many Veil Watchmen act alone, they often find themselves working closely with members of the Church of Octanoss and the Order of the Sentinels during their missions, and it’s not uncommon for these alliances to become full-fledged memberships with time. You can read more about the undead hunting renegades in the Church of Octanoss in the Underground Oracle Publishing release, Deities and Domains: Octanoss.</p></section><p></p><h2 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0px 0px 0.5rem;padding:0px;font-weight:normal;font-size:1.5em;border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header);color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Veil Watchman Magic</span></h2><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><em style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">3rd-level Veil Watchman feature</em></span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">You learn an additional spell when you reach certain levels in this class, as shown in the Veil Watchman Spells table. The spell counts as a ranger spell for you, but it doesn't count against the number of ranger spells you know.</span></p><table border=\"1\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:534px;border-collapse:collapse;background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-tertiary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-tertiary);margin:0.5em 0px;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><thead style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);color:var(--color-text-light-highlight);text-shadow:1px 1px var(--color-shadow-dark);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\"><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Ranger Level</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Spells</span></td></tr></thead><tbody style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">3rd</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.xmDBqZhRVrtLP8h2\" data-id=\"xmDBqZhRVrtLP8h2\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Protection from Evil and Good</a></span></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">5th</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.MK6gpQMeDFo0cP9f\" data-id=\"MK6gpQMeDFo0cP9f\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" aria-describedby=\"tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Continual Flame</a></span></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">9th</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.y8A4HfTwd93ypdEz\" data-id=\"y8A4HfTwd93ypdEz\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Magic Circle</a></span></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">13th</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.ImlCJQwR1VL40Qem\" data-id=\"ImlCJQwR1VL40Qem\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Arcane Eye</a></span></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">17th</span></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;padding:0.25em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-uuid=\"Compendium.dnd5e.spells.TkJ8Wtg1L7TZtspm\" data-id=\"TkJ8Wtg1L7TZtspm\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"dnd5e.spells\" data-tooltip=\"Spell Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;cursor:pointer;background:rgb(221, 221, 221);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Dispel Evil and Good</a></span></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><h2><strong>Hardened Aura</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.xkmvQOH96jwjVlA0]{Hardened Aura}</p><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><em style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">3rd-level Veil Watchman feature</em></span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Your specialized training has prepared you to face threats from the Ethereal. If an incorporeal creature attempts to move through you, it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw against your spell DC or it is immediately pushed back 5 feet and takes force damage as though it ended its turn inside an object.</span></p><p></p><h2><strong>Sunlit Edge</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.raUKtaDB42VW59XN]{Sunlit Edge}</p><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><em style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">3rd-level Veil Watchman feature</em></span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">You have learned to capture the purity of the sun to empower your attacks. Your attacks against undead count as magical for the purpose of overcoming resistance. Additionally, as a bonus action, you may choose one creature within 60 feet of you. The next time you hit that creature with an attack, you may deal an extra 1d8 radiant damage. This radiant damage counts as sunlight.</span></p><p></p><h2><strong>Reactive Anchor</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.umucUlUgKD9BdUdk]{Reactive Anchor}</p><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><em style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">7th-level Veil Watchman feature</em></span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">You’ve gained the ability to stop your ethereal opponents from retreating. When a creature within 60 feet of you attempts to possess a humanoid or enter the Ethereal Plane, you may use your reaction to anchor them. The target creature must make a Wisdom saving throw against your spell DC. On a failure, they cannot possess their target or enter the Ethereal Plane for a number of rounds equal to your proficiency bonus.</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a short or long rest.</span></p><p></p><h2><strong>Watchman's Vitality</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.apJcezOwLE26aZj7]{Watchman's Vitality}</p><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><em style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">11th-level Veil Watchman feature</em></span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;min-height:1rem;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Signika, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Your life of defending the veil against harmful spirits has granted you some protections against their draining presence. You gain resistance to necrotic damage and your hit point maximum cannot be reduced.</span></p><p></p><h2><strong>Veil Sight</strong></h2><p>@UUID[Item.dgcR40attOfinOW0]{Veil Sight}</p><p><em>15th-level Veil Watchman feature</em></p><p>The mastery of your esoteric craft has gifted you with the power to peer fully through the veil. You gain ethereal sight of 60 feet, allowing you to see into the Ethereal Plane.</p><p>Additionally, when you see a creature attempting to enter the Material Plane from the Ethereal Plane, you may use your reaction to make an immediate attack against that creature. If you successfully deal damage to the target creature, it may not enter the Material Plane for a number of rounds equal to your proficiency bonus.</p><img src=\"modules/under-the-harvest-moons/Assets/Art/veil_watchman2.png\" width=\"238\" height=\"358\" />","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1667069433116,"modifiedTime":1667786404500,"lastModifiedBy":"zr7Ai9kVc0jXui9g"},"_id":"esvXzekn2Q579V0q","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"YQ88Zx2ssDk4TvZ2":3}}
