e Features}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.ux6Jf0fW38BNg9XG.JournalEntryPage.qitGhP1vRMfLJEAJ#heprions-guide:-legendary-cursed-items]{Heprion's Guide: Legendary Cursed Items}</p><p></p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.esvXzekn2Q579V0q]{3. EERIE PLAYER OPTIONS}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.esvXzekn2Q579V0q.JournalEntryPage.8H8XgotkgmY1OQgT]{Lineage: Terrorborn}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.esvXzekn2Q579V0q.JournalEntryPage.8H8XgotkgmY1OQgT#nightmare-ancestry]{Nightmare Ancestry}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.esvXzekn2Q579V0q.JournalEntryPage.Sa5cXdOLXIXlSIfk]{Bardic College: College of the Curse Caller}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.esvXzekn2Q579V0q.JournalEntryPage.2dvBgWy93Y5YKkU8]{Cleric Domain: Broken Bone Domain}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.esvXzekn2Q579V0q.JournalEntryPage.T60tHd6HBnOGW9s2]{Druid Circle: Circle of the Unseely}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.esvXzekn2Q579V0q.JournalEntryPage.qXGjp2HBv4VQpeSw]{Ranger Archetype: Veil Watchman}</p><p></p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.3LU2sPcRUAi8hV6j]{4. SINISTER CREATURE OPTIONS}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.3LU2sPcRUAi8hV6j.JournalEntryPage.sft14KecdhxyUmKR]{Monsters Mythica: Black-Eyed Child}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.3LU2sPcRUAi8hV6j.JournalEntryPage.9Dy5Nzc0o2NFnxPa]{Monsters Mythica: Dread Coachman}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.3LU2sPcRUAi8hV6j.JournalEntryPage.JL15BnLKLqipsetq]{Monsters Mythica: Terrors of the Deep Woods - Bunny Man}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.3LU2sPcRUAi8hV6j.JournalEntryPage.dhfO5t5S2Rt9CHn1]{Monsters Mythica: Terrors of the Deep Woods - Not Deer}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.3LU2sPcRUAi8hV6j.JournalEntryPage.zJJp37phl63UTxoP]{Monsters Mythica: Terrors of the Deep Woods - White Thing}</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":0,"name":"Introduction","type":"text","_id":"BgD8Uqp6qx9E3z5h","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p></p><blockquote><p>The moons hang heavy and full in the skies, and with them, our hopes for the coming season. We are almost at our time of peace, of rest and contemplation under blankets of snow. But for now, the realms are not ours. They belong to the creatures of darkness and shadow. To those beings who creep past the veil and seek to take their claim on a world caught In-Between. Be wary now, child, and do not stray after sundown. Though the skies seem bright, the light of the harvest moons does not shine for us.</p></blockquote><p></p><p>In the following pages, you’ll be presented with options to add a dose of delightful dread to your 5th edition games. From the gothic to the gruesome, from folk horror to body horror, there is something contained within for all manner of spine-chilling campaigns and encounters.</p><p>Explore the origins and games of Pallowen, the festival of the Frightful Harvest. Fend off the sadistic goals of the cult of the Broken Bone or introduce your PCs to ghastly creatures taken from myth and urban legend. Embody the new terrorborn lineage and discover your own nightmarish ancestry or join the Order of the Sentinels and stand against the existential threats that would harm the realms of mortals. Use the many options presented to sculpt a horrid masterpiece that is uniquely yours.</p><p>We have provided you with the tools you need to haunt your world; how you choose to do so is where the true fun begins.</p><p></p><img src=\"modules/under-the-harvest-moons/Assets/Art/into.jpg\" />","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":-200000,"name":"OGL","type":"text","_id":"Amle5X1B7MV3g8DA","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><strong>OGL Legal Information OPEN GAME License Version 1.0a The following text is the property of Wizards of the Coast, LLC. and is Copyright 2000 Wizards of the Coast, Inc (\"Wizards\"). All Rights Reserved. 1. Definitions: (a)\"Contributors\" means the copyright and/ or trademark owners who have contributed O